 data-end=\"491\"><strong data-start=\"448\" data-end=\"476\">Semax Molecular Formula:</strong> C₃₇H₅₁N₉O₁₀S</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"492\" data-end=\"536\">\n<p data-start=\"494\" data-end=\"536\"><strong data-start=\"494\" data-end=\"521\">Semax Molecular Weight:</strong> 813.93 g/mol</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"537\" data-end=\"588\">\n<p data-start=\"539\" data-end=\"588\"><strong data-start=\"539\" data-end=\"558\">Semax Sequence:</strong> Met-Glu-His-Phe-Pro-Gly-Pro</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"590\" data-end=\"688\">\n<p data-start=\"592\" data-end=\"688\"><strong data-start=\"592\" data-end=\"616\">Molecular Structure:</strong> Refer to Certificate of Analysis for detailed structural information.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"690\" data-end=\"1246\"><strong data-start=\"690\" data-end=\"706\">Description:</strong><br data-start=\"706\" data-end=\"709\" />The Selank / Semax Blend is a combination of two synthetic heptapeptides extensively studied for their roles in neurological and cognitive research. Selank, derived from tuftsin, is studied for its effects on stress response, immune balance, and anxiolytic pathways. Semax, derived from an ACTH fragment, is studied for its neuromodulatory and neuroprotective properties. Together, this blend offers a unique research tool for investigating overlapping and complementary mechanisms in cognition, neuroprotection, and stress modulation.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1248\" data-end=\"1350\"><strong data-start=\"1248\" data-end=\"1274\">Research Applications:</strong><br data-start=\"1274\" data-end=\"1277\" />The Selank / Semax Blend is actively researched for potential roles in:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"1352\" data-end=\"1847\">\n<li data-start=\"1352\" data-end=\"1433\">\n<p data-start=\"1354\" data-end=\"1433\"><strong data-start=\"1354\" data-end=\"1377\">Cognitive Function:</strong> Investigating effects on memory, learning, and focus.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1434\" data-end=\"1528\">\n<p data-start=\"1436\" data-end=\"1528\"><strong data-start=\"1436\" data-end=\"1464\">Stress &amp; Anxiety Models:</strong> Studying modulation of stress-related and GABAergic pathways.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1529\" data-end=\"1640\">\n<p data-start=\"1531\" data-end=\"1640\"><strong data-start=\"1531\" data-end=\"1551\">Neuroprotection:</strong> Exploring protective effects against oxidative stress and neurodegenerative processes.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1641\" data-end=\"1742\">\n<p data-start=\"1643\" data-end=\"1742\"><strong data-start=\"1643\" data-end=\"1665\">Immune Regulation:</strong> Evaluating Selank’s role in balancing immune responses in research models.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1743\" data-end=\"1847\">\n<p data-start=\"1745\" data-end=\"1847\"><strong data-start=\"1745\" data-end=\"1769\">Synergistic Effects:</strong> Assessing combined influence on neurological health and adaptive responses.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"1849\" data-end=\"1876\"><strong data-start=\"1849\" data-end=\"1874\">Storage and Handling:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1878\" data-end=\"2093\">\n<li data-start=\"1878\" data-end=\"1938\">\n<p data-start=\"1880\" data-end=\"1938\">Store lyophilized powder at -20°C in a sealed container.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1939\" data-end=\"1995\">\n<p data-start=\"1941\" data-end=\"1995\">Once reconstituted, store at 2-8°C and use promptly.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1996\" data-end=\"2034\">\n<p data-start=\"1998\" data-end=\"2034\">Avoid repeated freeze-thaw cycles.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2035\" data-end=\"2093\">\n<p data-start=\"2037\" data-end=\"2093\">Handle using aseptic techniques to maintain integrity.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"2095\" data-end=\"2124\"><strong data-start=\"2095\" data-end=\"2122\">Product Specifications:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"2126\" data-end=\"2260\">\n<li data-start=\"2126\" data-end=\"2158\">\n<p data-start=\"2128\" data-end=\"2158\">Purity: ≥99% (HPLC Verified)</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2159\" data-end=\"2212\">\n<p data-start=\"2161\" data-end=\"2212\">Appearance: White to off-white lyophilized powder</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2213\" data-end=\"2260\">\n<p data-start=\"2215\" data-end=\"2260\">Solubility: Soluble in bacteriostatic water</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"2262\" data-end=\"2851\"><strong data-start=\"2262\" data-end=\"2281\">Important Note:</strong><br data-start=\"2281\" data-end=\"2284\" />This product is strictly FOR RESEARCH USE ONLY and is intended exclusively for in vitro research and laboratory experimentation by qualified professionals. It is not a drug, food, cosmetic, or dietary supplement, and has not been evaluated by the FDA. This peptide is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. The bodily introduction into humans or animals is strictly prohibited by law. Any misuse, misbranding, or mislabeling is a violation of federal regulations and may result in legal action under applicable federal, state, or local laws.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2853\" data-end=\"2916\"><strong data-start=\"2853\" data-end=\"2868\">References:</strong><br data-start=\"2868\" data-end=\"2871\" />Referenced scientific publications include:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"2918\" data-end=\"3434\">\n<li data-start=\"2918\" data-end=\"3031\">\n<p data-start=\"2920\" data-end=\"3031\">Ashmarin, I. P., et al. (2000). “Semax: A New Neuroprotective Peptide.” Neuroscience &amp; Behavioral Physiology.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"3032\" data-end=\"3161\">\n<p data-start=\"3034\" data-end=\"3161\">Myasoedov, N. F., et al. (2008). “The Role of Semax in Neuroprotection and Cognitive Enhancement.” Journal of Neurochemistry.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"3162\" data-end=\"3298\">\n<p data-start=\"3164\" data-end=\"3298\">Medvedev, A. E., et al. (2005). “Neuropeptide Selank: Behavioral and Neurochemical Studies.” Neuroscience and Behavioral Physiology.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"3299\" data-end=\"3434\">\n<p data-start=\"3301\" data-end=\"3434\">Dolotov, O. V., et al. (2010). “Anxiolytic-Like Effects of Selank in Animal Models.” Bulletin of Experimental Biology and Medicine.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>',134.00,78.00,NULL,10.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/SelankSemax_1010mg-Card-scaled.jpg','https://myoasislabs.com/product/selank-semax-10mg-blend/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 13:37:06',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,62),(66,'GLOW 70mg GHK-CU/BPC-157/TB-500 50/10/10mg Blend','<p>All Oasis Labs products are third-party tested by clinical labs to ensure maximum purity.</p>',150.00,99.00,NULL,70.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/GLOW-70mgv2-scaled.jpg','https://myoasislabs.com/product/glow-70mg-ghk-cu-bpc-157-tb-500-50-10-10mg-blend/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 19:42:58',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,7),(67,'KLOW 80mg GHK-CU/BPC-157/TB-500/KPV 50/10/10/10mg Blend','<p>All Oasis Labs products are third-party tested by clinical labs to ensure maximum purity.</p>',183.00,119.00,NULL,80.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/KLOW_80mg-Cardv2-scaled.jpg','https://myoasislabs.com/product/klow/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 19:44:06',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,113),(68,'TESA/IPA Blend 10/1mg','<p data-start=\"161\" data-end=\"247\"><strong data-start=\"181\" data-end=\"247\">Tesa / Ipamorelin Blend – 10 mg / 1 mg Lyophilized Vial</strong></p>\n<hr data-start=\"249\" data-end=\"252\" />\n<p data-start=\"254\" data-end=\"281\"><strong data-start=\"254\" data-end=\"279\">Chemical Information:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"282\" data-end=\"556\">\n<li data-start=\"282\" data-end=\"336\">\n<p data-start=\"284\" data-end=\"336\"><strong data-start=\"284\" data-end=\"318\">Tesa Molecular Formula:</strong> C₂₂₁H₃₆₆N₇₂O₆₇S</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"337\" data-end=\"387\">\n<p data-start=\"339\" data-end=\"387\"><strong data-start=\"339\" data-end=\"372\">Tesa Molecular Weight:</strong> 5135.9 g/mol</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"388\" data-end=\"436\">\n<p data-start=\"390\" data-end=\"436\"><strong data-start=\"390\" data-end=\"423\">Ipamorelin Molecular Formula:</strong> C₃₈H₄₉N₉O₅</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"437\" data-end=\"486\">\n<p data-start=\"439\" data-end=\"486\"><strong data-start=\"439\" data-end=\"471\">Ipamorelin Molecular Weight:</strong> 711.86 g/mol</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"487\" data-end=\"556\">\n<p data-start=\"489\" data-end=\"556\"><strong data-start=\"489\" data-end=\"510\">Formulation Type:</strong> Lyophilized powder blend for reconstitution</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"558\" data-end=\"561\" />\n<p data-start=\"563\" data-end=\"905\"><strong data-start=\"563\" data-end=\"579\">Description:</strong><br data-start=\"579\" data-end=\"582\" />This research blend combines <strong data-start=\"611\" data-end=\"626\">Tesa</strong>, a potent Growth Hormone-Releasing Hormone (GHRH) analog, with <strong data-start=\"690\" data-end=\"704\">Ipamorelin</strong>, a selective Growth Hormone Secretagogue Receptor (GHSR) agonist. The combination is designed for synergistic study of pulsatile growth hormone release and IGF-1 modulation in experimental settings.</p>\n<p data-start=\"907\" data-end=\"1185\">Tesamorelin acts primarily at the pituitary level to stimulate natural growth hormone production via GHRH receptor activation, while Ipamorelin selectively stimulates ghrelin receptors to complement and enhance GH release without significantly affecting cortisol or prolactin.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"1187\" data-end=\"1190\" />\n<p data-start=\"1192\" data-end=\"1290\"><strong data-start=\"1192\" data-end=\"1218\">Research Applications:</strong><br data-start=\"1218\" data-end=\"1221\" />The Tesa / Ipamorelin blend is studied for its potential to:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"1291\" data-end=\"1714\">\n<li data-start=\"1291\" data-end=\"1364\">\n<p data-start=\"1293\" data-end=\"1364\"><strong data-start=\"1293\" data-end=\"1329\">Enhance Growth Hormone Secretion</strong> through dual-pathway stimulation</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1365\" data-end=\"1440\">\n<p data-start=\"1367\" data-end=\"1440\"><strong data-start=\"1367\" data-end=\"1415\">Investigate Synergistic GH &amp; IGF-1 Increases</strong> in experimental models</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1441\" data-end=\"1527\">\n<p data-start=\"1443\" data-end=\"1527\"><strong data-start=\"1443\" data-end=\"1477\">Study Body Composition Changes</strong>, including lean mass support and fat metabolism</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1528\" data-end=\"1622\">\n<p data-start=\"1530\" data-end=\"1622\"><strong data-start=\"1530\" data-end=\"1560\">Evaluate Metabolic Effects</strong> on glucose handling, lipid profiles, and energy expenditure</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1623\" data-end=\"1714\">\n<p data-start=\"1625\" data-end=\"1714\"><strong data-start=\"1625\" data-end=\"1658\">Explore Anti-Aging Mechanisms</strong> related to GH-mediated tissue repair and regeneration</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1716\" data-end=\"1719\" />\n<p data-start=\"1721\" data-end=\"1748\"><strong data-start=\"1721\" data-end=\"1746\">Storage and Handling:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1749\" data-end=\"1963\">\n<li data-start=\"1749\" data-end=\"1799\">\n<p data-start=\"1751\" data-end=\"1799\">Store lyophilized vials at <strong data-start=\"1778\" data-end=\"1787\">-20°C</strong> until use</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1800\" data-end=\"1861\">\n<p data-start=\"1802\" data-end=\"1861\">After reconstitution, store at <strong data-start=\"1833\" data-end=\"1842\">2–8°C</strong> and use promptly</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1862\" data-end=\"1899\">\n<p data-start=\"1864\" data-end=\"1899\">Avoid repeated freeze-thaw cycles</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1900\" data-end=\"1963\">\n<p data-start=\"1902\" data-end=\"1963\">Use aseptic techniques during reconstitution and withdrawal</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1965\" data-end=\"1968\" />\n<p data-start=\"1970\" data-end=\"1999\"><strong data-start=\"1970\" data-end=\"1997\">Product Specifications:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"2000\" data-end=\"2304\">\n<li data-start=\"2000\" data-end=\"2038\">\n<p data-start=\"2002\" data-end=\"2038\"><strong data-start=\"2002\" data-end=\"2011\">Form:</strong> Lyophilized powder blend</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2039\" data-end=\"2106\">\n<p data-start=\"2041\" data-end=\"2106\"><strong data-start=\"2041\" data-end=\"2059\">Concentration:</strong> 10 mg Tesa + 1 mg Ipamorelin per vial</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2107\" data-end=\"2160\">\n<p data-start=\"2109\" data-end=\"2160\"><strong data-start=\"2109\" data-end=\"2120\">Purity:</strong> ≥99% (HPLC Verified) for each peptide</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2161\" data-end=\"2206\">\n<p data-start=\"2163\" data-end=\"2206\"><strong data-start=\"2163\" data-end=\"2178\">Appearance:</strong> White lyophilized powder</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2207\" data-end=\"2304\">\n<p data-start=\"2209\" data-end=\"2304\"><strong data-start=\"2209\" data-end=\"2224\">Solubility:</strong> Soluble in bacteriostatic water for research purposes</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"2306\" data-end=\"2309\" />\n<p data-start=\"2311\" data-end=\"2754\"><strong data-start=\"2311\" data-end=\"2330\">Important Note:</strong><br data-start=\"2330\" data-end=\"2333\" /><strong data-start=\"2333\" data-end=\"2392\">For Research Use Only – Not for Human or Veterinary Use</strong><br data-start=\"2392\" data-end=\"2395\" />This product is intended solely for in vitro research and laboratory use by qualified professionals. It is not a drug, food, or dietary supplement and has not been evaluated by the FDA. It is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Any bodily administration to humans or animals is strictly prohibited and may violate applicable laws.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2756\" data-end=\"2759\" />\n<p data-start=\"2761\" data-end=\"2778\"><strong data-start=\"2761\" data-end=\"2776\">References:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"2779\" data-end=\"3175\">\n<li data-start=\"2779\" data-end=\"2939\">\n<p data-start=\"2781\" data-end=\"2939\">Falutz, J., et al. (2010). <em data-start=\"2808\" data-end=\"2913\">“Effects of Tesamorelin on Abdominal Fat and IGF-1 Levels in HIV-Infected Patients with Lipodystrophy.”</em> J Clin Endocrinol Metab</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2940\" data-end=\"3050\">\n<p data-start=\"2942\" data-end=\"3050\">Raun, K., et al. (1998). <em data-start=\"2967\" data-end=\"3031\">“Ipamorelin, the first selective growth hormone secretagogue.”</em> Eur J Endocrinol</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"3051\" data-end=\"3175\">\n<p data-start=\"3053\" data-end=\"3175\">Perry, J., et al. (2020). <em data-start=\"3079\" data-end=\"3153\">“Synergistic Effects of GHRH Analogues and GHSR Agonists on GH Release.”</em> Growth Horm IGF Res</p>\n</li>\n</ul>',122.00,79.00,NULL,1.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/TesaIpa_101mg-card-scaled.jpg','https://myoasislabs.com/product/tesaipa-10mg/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 13:37:06',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,65),(69,'GHK-Cu 50mg','<p data-start=\"37\" data-end=\"64\"><strong data-start=\"37\" data-end=\"62\">Chemical Information:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"65\" data-end=\"270\">\n<li data-start=\"65\" data-end=\"104\"><strong data-start=\"67\" data-end=\"89\">Molecular Formula:</strong> C₁₄H₂₄N₆O₄Cu</li>\n<li data-start=\"105\" data-end=\"143\"><strong data-start=\"107\" data-end=\"128\">Molecular Weight:</strong> 340.84 g/mol</li>\n<li data-start=\"144\" data-end=\"173\"><strong data-start=\"146\" data-end=\"159\">Sequence:</strong> Gly-His-Lys</li>\n<li data-start=\"174\" data-end=\"270\"><strong data-start=\"176\" data-end=\"200\">Molecular Structure:</strong> Refer to Certificate of Analysis for detailed structural information.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"272\" data-end=\"275\" />\n<p data-start=\"277\" data-end=\"915\"><strong data-start=\"277\" data-end=\"293\">Description:</strong><br data-start=\"293\" data-end=\"296\" />GHK-Cu (glycyl-L-histidyl-L-lysine copper) is a naturally occurring copper peptide extensively studied in laboratory research for its potential roles in tissue remodeling, cellular repair processes, and wound healing. Comprised of three amino acids—glycine, histidine, and lysine—complexed with copper ions, GHK-Cu has been investigated for its capacity to stimulate collagen production, regulate inflammatory pathways, and support skin and hair follicle health. Provided in lyophilized powder form, GHK-Cu is suitable for research into cellular repair mechanisms, dermatological processes, and inflammation modulation.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"917\" data-end=\"920\" />\n<p data-start=\"922\" data-end=\"1024\"><strong data-start=\"922\" data-end=\"948\">Research Applications:</strong><br data-start=\"948\" data-end=\"951\" />Laboratory studies involving GHK-Cu typically explore its potential to:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"1025\" data-end=\"1496\">\n<li data-start=\"1025\" data-end=\"1124\"><strong data-start=\"1027\" data-end=\"1053\">Enhance Wound Healing:</strong> Examine effects on tissue regeneration and cellular repair pathways.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1125\" data-end=\"1251\"><strong data-start=\"1127\" data-end=\"1151\">Support Skin Health:</strong> Investigate its role in collagen synthesis, elasticity, and structural integrity of skin tissues.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1252\" data-end=\"1374\"><strong data-start=\"1254\" data-end=\"1280\">Modulate Inflammation:</strong> Evaluate potential anti-inflammatory effects in both acute and chronic experimental models.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1375\" data-end=\"1496\"><strong data-start=\"1377\" data-end=\"1406\">Stimulate Hair Follicles:</strong> Study effects on hair follicle activity and related mechanisms that may reduce hair loss.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1498\" data-end=\"1501\" />\n<p data-start=\"1503\" data-end=\"1530\"><strong data-start=\"1503\" data-end=\"1528\">Storage and Handling:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1531\" data-end=\"1724\">\n<li data-start=\"1531\" data-end=\"1573\">Store lyophilized powder at <strong data-start=\"1561\" data-end=\"1570\">-20°C</strong>.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1574\" data-end=\"1642\">After reconstitution, refrigerate at <strong data-start=\"1613\" data-end=\"1622\">2-8°C</strong> and use promptly.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1643\" data-end=\"1724\">Maintain aseptic handling procedures to ensure sterility and product integrity.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1726\" data-end=\"1729\" />\n<p data-start=\"1731\" data-end=\"1760\"><strong data-start=\"1731\" data-end=\"1758\">Product Specifications:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1761\" data-end=\"1892\">\n<li data-start=\"1761\" data-end=\"1797\"><strong data-start=\"1763\" data-end=\"1774\">Purity:</strong> ≥99% (HPLC Verified)</li>\n<li data-start=\"1798\" data-end=\"1842\"><strong data-start=\"1800\" data-end=\"1815\">Appearance:</strong> Lyophilized blue powder</li>\n<li data-start=\"1843\" data-end=\"1892\"><strong data-start=\"1845\" data-end=\"1860\">Solubility:</strong> Soluble in bacteriostatic water</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1894\" data-end=\"1897\" />\n<p data-start=\"1899\" data-end=\"2494\"><strong data-start=\"1899\" data-end=\"1918\">Important Note:</strong><br data-start=\"1918\" data-end=\"1921\" />This product is strictly <strong data-start=\"1946\" data-end=\"1971\">FOR RESEARCH USE ONLY</strong> and is intended exclusively for in vitro research and laboratory experimentation by qualified professionals. It is <strong data-start=\"2087\" data-end=\"2094\">not</strong> a drug, food, cosmetic, or dietary supplement, and has not been evaluated by the FDA. This peptide is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. The bodily introduction into humans or animals is strictly prohibited by law. Any misuse, misbranding, or mislabeling is a violation of federal regulations and may result in legal action under applicable federal, state, or local laws.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2496\" data-end=\"2499\" />\n<p data-start=\"2501\" data-end=\"2562\"><strong data-start=\"2501\" data-end=\"2516\">References:</strong><br data-start=\"2516\" data-end=\"2519\" />Referenced scientific publications include:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"2564\" data-end=\"2845\" data-is-only-node=\"\" data-is-last-node=\"\">\n<li data-start=\"2564\" data-end=\"2732\">Maquart, F. X., et al. (1993). <em data-start=\"2597\" data-end=\"2698\">“Stimulation of Collagen Synthesis in Fibroblast Cultures by the Tripeptide-Copper Complex GHK-Cu.”</em> Journal of Cellular Physiology.</li>\n<li data-start=\"2733\" data-end=\"2845\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Pickart, L., et al. (2008). <em data-start=\"2763\" data-end=\"2814\">“The Human Tripeptide GHK and Tissue Remodeling.”</em> Biomedicine &amp; Pharmacotherapy.</li>\n</ul>',82.00,34.00,NULL,50.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/GHK-CU_50mg-Card-1-scaled.jpg','https://myoasislabs.com/product/ghk-cu-50mg/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 13:37:06',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,51),(70,'5-Amino-1MQ 10 mg','<p data-start=\"109\" data-end=\"169\"><strong data-start=\"129\" data-end=\"169\">5-Amino-1MQ – 10 mg Lyophilized Vial</strong></p>\n<hr data-start=\"171\" data-end=\"174\" />\n<p data-start=\"176\" data-end=\"203\"><strong data-start=\"176\" data-end=\"201\">Chemical Information:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"204\" data-end=\"395\">\n<li data-start=\"204\" data-end=\"238\">\n<p data-start=\"206\" data-end=\"238\"><strong data-start=\"206\" data-end=\"228\">Molecular Formula:</strong> C₇H₁₁N₅</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"239\" data-end=\"277\">\n<p data-start=\"241\" data-end=\"277\"><strong data-start=\"241\" data-end=\"262\">Molecular Weight:</strong> 165.20 g/mol</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"278\" data-end=\"331\">\n<p data-start=\"280\" data-end=\"331\"><strong data-start=\"280\" data-end=\"298\">Chemical Name:</strong> 5-Amino-1-methylquinolin-1-ium</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"332\" data-end=\"395\">\n<p data-start=\"334\" data-end=\"395\"><strong data-start=\"334\" data-end=\"355\">Formulation Type:</strong> Lyophilized powder for reconstitution</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"397\" data-end=\"400\" />\n<p data-start=\"402\" data-end=\"878\"><strong data-start=\"402\" data-end=\"418\">Description:</strong><br />\n5-Amino-1MQ is a small-molecule experimental compound that functions as a <strong data-start=\"495\" data-end=\"526\">methyltransferase inhibitor</strong>, particularly targeting <strong data-start=\"551\" data-end=\"594\">nicotinamide N-methyltransferase (NNMT)</strong>. This enzyme plays a role in regulating cellular energy metabolism, making 5-Amino-1MQ a focus of research into obesity, metabolic disorders, and age-related energy decline. By modulating NNMT activity, 5-Amino-1MQ may influence NAD⁺ levels and energy balance in experimental models.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"880\" data-end=\"883\" />\n<p data-start=\"885\" data-end=\"966\"><strong data-start=\"885\" data-end=\"911\">Research Applications:</strong><br />\n5-Amino-1MQ is being studied for its potential to:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"967\" data-end=\"1339\">\n<li data-start=\"967\" data-end=\"1061\">\n<p data-start=\"969\" data-end=\"1061\"><strong data-start=\"969\" data-end=\"1007\">Support Weight Management Research</strong> by modulating metabolic rate and energy expenditure</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1062\" data-end=\"1125\">\n<p data-start=\"1064\" data-end=\"1125\"><strong data-start=\"1064\" data-end=\"1095\">Investigate NNMT Inhibition</strong> in metabolic disease models</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1126\" data-end=\"1196\">\n<p data-start=\"1128\" data-end=\"1196\"><strong data-start=\"1128\" data-end=\"1166\">Enhance Cellular Energy Metabolism</strong> via NAD⁺ pathway regulation</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1197\" data-end=\"1270\">\n<p data-start=\"1199\" data-end=\"1270\"><strong data-start=\"1199\" data-end=\"1240\">Explore Age-Related Metabolic Decline</strong> and potential interventions</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1271\" data-end=\"1339\">\n<p data-start=\"1273\" data-end=\"1339\"><strong data-start=\"1273\" data-end=\"1314\">Evaluate Lipid and Glucose Metabolism</strong> in preclinical studies</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1341\" data-end=\"1344\" />\n<p data-start=\"1346\" data-end=\"1373\"><strong data-start=\"1346\" data-end=\"1371\">Storage and Handling:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1374\" data-end=\"1564\">\n<li data-start=\"1374\" data-end=\"1415\">\n<p data-start=\"1376\" data-end=\"1415\">Store lyophilized powder at <strong data-start=\"1404\" data-end=\"1413\">-20°C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1416\" data-end=\"1477\">\n<p data-start=\"1418\" data-end=\"1477\">After reconstitution, store at <strong data-start=\"1449\" data-end=\"1458\">2–8°C</strong> and use promptly</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1478\" data-end=\"1515\">\n<p data-start=\"1480\" data-end=\"1515\">Avoid repeated freeze-thaw cycles</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1516\" data-end=\"1564\">\n<p data-start=\"1518\" data-end=\"1564\">Use aseptic techniques to maintain sterility</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1566\" data-end=\"1569\" />\n<p data-start=\"1571\" data-end=\"1600\"><strong data-start=\"1571\" data-end=\"1598\">Product Specifications:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1601\" data-end=\"1857\">\n<li data-start=\"1601\" data-end=\"1633\">\n<p data-start=\"1603\" data-end=\"1633\"><strong data-start=\"1603\" data-end=\"1612\">Form:</strong> Lyophilized powder</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1634\" data-end=\"1671\">\n<p data-start=\"1636\" data-end=\"1671\"><strong data-start=\"1636\" data-end=\"1654\">Concentration:</strong> 10 mg per vial</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1672\" data-end=\"1708\">\n<p data-start=\"1674\" data-end=\"1708\"><strong data-start=\"1674\" data-end=\"1685\">Purity:</strong> ≥99% (HPLC Verified)</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1709\" data-end=\"1754\">\n<p data-start=\"1711\" data-end=\"1754\"><strong data-start=\"1711\" data-end=\"1726\">Appearance:</strong> Orange powder</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1755\" data-end=\"1857\">\n<p data-start=\"1757\" data-end=\"1857\"><strong data-start=\"1757\" data-end=\"1772\">Solubility:</strong> Soluble in bacteriostatic water, DMSO, or other suitable solvents for research use</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1859\" data-end=\"1862\" />\n<p data-start=\"1864\" data-end=\"2415\"><strong data-start=\"1864\" data-end=\"1883\">Important Note:</strong><br />\n<strong data-start=\"1886\" data-end=\"1945\">For Research Use Only – Not for Human or Veterinary Use</strong><br />\nThis product is intended strictly for in vitro research and laboratory experimentation by qualified professionals. It is not a drug, food, cosmetic, or dietary supplement and has not been evaluated by the FDA. It is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. The bodily introduction of this product into humans or animals is strictly prohibited by law. Any misuse, misbranding, or mislabeling of this product is a violation of federal regulations.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2417\" data-end=\"2420\" />\n<p data-start=\"2422\" data-end=\"2439\"><strong data-start=\"2422\" data-end=\"2437\">References:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"2440\" data-end=\"2833\">\n<li data-start=\"2440\" data-end=\"2562\">\n<p data-start=\"2442\" data-end=\"2562\">Kraus, D., et al. (2014). <em data-start=\"2468\" data-end=\"2553\">“Nicotinamide N-methyltransferase knockdown protects against diet-induced obesity.”</em> Nature</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2563\" data-end=\"2691\">\n<p data-start=\"2565\" data-end=\"2691\">Hong, S., et al. (2018). <em data-start=\"2590\" data-end=\"2658\">“NNMT Inhibitors as a Therapeutic Option for Metabolic Disorders.”</em> Journal of Medicinal Chemistry</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2692\" data-end=\"2833\">\n<p data-start=\"2694\" data-end=\"2833\">Policarpo, R., et al. (2020). <em data-start=\"2724\" data-end=\"2799\">“Development of Potent NNMT Inhibitors for Modulating Energy Metabolism.”</em> ACS Medicinal Chemistry Letters</p>\n</li>\n</ul>',98.00,67.00,NULL,10.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/unASDSAASDAASDASDASDSADSASDASDASDASDADASDADtitled-scaled.jpg','https://myoasislabs.com/product/5-amino-1mq-10-mg/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 13:37:06',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,4),(71,'GLP3(R) 30mg','<p data-start=\"75\" data-end=\"102\"><strong data-start=\"75\" data-end=\"100\">Chemical Information:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"103\" data-end=\"346\">\n<li data-start=\"103\" data-end=\"146\"><strong data-start=\"105\" data-end=\"127\">Molecular Formula:</strong> C₂₂₃H₃₄₃F₃N₄₆O₇₀</li>\n<li data-start=\"147\" data-end=\"186\"><strong data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"170\">Molecular Weight:</strong> 4845.44 g/mol</li>\n<li data-start=\"187\" data-end=\"249\"><strong data-start=\"189\" data-end=\"202\">Sequence:</strong> YA1QGTFTSDYSIL2LDKK4AQA1AFIEYLLEGGPSSGAPPPS3</li>\n<li data-start=\"250\" data-end=\"346\"><strong data-start=\"252\" data-end=\"276\">Molecular Structure:</strong> Refer to Certificate of Analysis for detailed structural information.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"348\" data-end=\"351\" />\n<p data-start=\"353\" data-end=\"834\"><strong data-start=\"353\" data-end=\"369\">Description:</strong><br data-start=\"369\" data-end=\"372\" />GLP3(R) is a synthetic peptide currently under research as a tri-agonist for GLP-1, GIP, and glucagon receptors. It is extensively studied in laboratory environments for its potential influence on metabolic regulation, including energy balance, lipid metabolism, glucose signaling, and related cellular pathways. Provided in lyophilized powder form, GLP3(R) facilitates controlled in vitro investigations into metabolic processes and endocrine signaling.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"836\" data-end=\"839\" />\n<p data-start=\"841\" data-end=\"930\"><strong data-start=\"841\" data-end=\"867\">Research Applications:</strong><br data-start=\"867\" data-end=\"870\" />GLP3(R) is actively researched for potential roles in:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"931\" data-end=\"1535\">\n<li data-start=\"931\" data-end=\"1086\"><strong data-start=\"933\" data-end=\"966\">Glucose and Insulin Pathways:</strong> Investigating signaling mechanisms associated with insulin sensitivity and glucose metabolism in experimental models.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1087\" data-end=\"1240\"><strong data-start=\"1089\" data-end=\"1129\">Energy Balance and Appetite Control:</strong> Studying peptide interactions affecting energy intake, appetite regulation, and related metabolic responses.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1241\" data-end=\"1366\"><strong data-start=\"1243\" data-end=\"1264\">Lipid Metabolism:</strong> Exploring effects on lipid profiles, fatty acid metabolism, and related metabolic markers in vitro.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1367\" data-end=\"1535\"><strong data-start=\"1369\" data-end=\"1400\">Hepatic Cellular Responses:</strong> Evaluating potential roles in liver-related cellular activities, including lipid accumulation, inflammation, and metabolic regulation.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1537\" data-end=\"1540\" />\n<p data-start=\"1542\" data-end=\"1569\"><strong data-start=\"1542\" data-end=\"1567\">Storage and Handling:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1570\" data-end=\"1762\">\n<li data-start=\"1570\" data-end=\"1612\">Store lyophilized powder at <strong data-start=\"1600\" data-end=\"1609\">-20°C</strong>.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1613\" data-end=\"1681\">After reconstitution, refrigerate at <strong data-start=\"1652\" data-end=\"1661\">2-8°C</strong> and use promptly.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1682\" data-end=\"1762\">Maintain aseptic handling practices to ensure sterility and product integrity.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1764\" data-end=\"1767\" />\n<p data-start=\"1769\" data-end=\"1798\"><strong data-start=\"1769\" data-end=\"1796\">Product Specifications:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1799\" data-end=\"1930\">\n<li data-start=\"1799\" data-end=\"1835\"><strong data-start=\"1801\" data-end=\"1812\">Purity:</strong> ≥99% (HPLC Verified)</li>\n<li data-start=\"1836\" data-end=\"1880\"><strong data-start=\"1838\" data-end=\"1853\">Appearance:</strong> Lyophilized white powder</li>\n<li data-start=\"1881\" data-end=\"1930\"><strong data-start=\"1883\" data-end=\"1898\">Solubility:</strong> Soluble in bacteriostatic water</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1932\" data-end=\"1935\" />\n<p data-start=\"1937\" data-end=\"2532\"><strong data-start=\"1937\" data-end=\"1956\">Important Note:</strong><br data-start=\"1956\" data-end=\"1959\" />This product is strictly <strong data-start=\"1984\" data-end=\"2009\">FOR RESEARCH USE ONLY</strong> and is intended exclusively for in vitro research and laboratory experimentation by qualified professionals. It is <strong data-start=\"2125\" data-end=\"2132\">not</strong> a drug, food, cosmetic, or dietary supplement, and has not been evaluated by the FDA. This peptide is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. The bodily introduction into humans or animals is strictly prohibited by law. Any misuse, misbranding, or mislabeling is a violation of federal regulations and may result in legal action under applicable federal, state, or local laws.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2534\" data-end=\"2537\" />\n<p data-start=\"2539\" data-end=\"2600\"><strong data-start=\"2539\" data-end=\"2554\">References:</strong><br data-start=\"2554\" data-end=\"2557\" />Referenced scientific publications include:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"2602\" data-end=\"2858\" data-is-only-node=\"\" data-is-last-node=\"\">\n<li data-start=\"2602\" data-end=\"2746\">Jastreboff, A. M., et al. (2022). <em data-start=\"2638\" data-end=\"2711\">“GLP3(R) for the Management of Obesity: A Multi-Receptor Approach.”</em> New England Journal of Medicine.</li>\n<li data-start=\"2747\" data-end=\"2858\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Mehta, A., et al. (2023). <em data-start=\"2775\" data-end=\"2843\">“Mechanistic Insights into GLP3(R)&#8217;s Triple Receptor Agonism.”</em> Diabetes Care.</li>\n</ul>',700.00,289.00,NULL,30.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/glp3-30-scaled.jpeg','https://myoasislabs.com/product/glp3r-30mg-reta/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 21:39:28',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,347),(72,'L-Carnitine 500mg/ml 10ml Vial','<p data-start=\"144\" data-end=\"171\"><strong data-start=\"144\" data-end=\"169\">Chemical Information:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"172\" data-end=\"313\">\n<li data-start=\"172\" data-end=\"207\">\n<p data-start=\"174\" data-end=\"207\"><strong data-start=\"174\" data-end=\"196\">Molecular Formula:</strong> C₇H₁₅NO₃</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"208\" data-end=\"246\">\n<p data-start=\"210\" data-end=\"246\"><strong data-start=\"210\" data-end=\"231\">Molecular Weight:</strong> 161.20 g/mol</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"247\" data-end=\"313\">\n<p data-start=\"249\" data-end=\"313\"><strong data-start=\"249\" data-end=\"267\">Chemical Name:</strong> (R)-3-Hydroxy-4-(trimethylammonio)butanoate</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"315\" data-end=\"318\" />\n<p data-start=\"320\" data-end=\"888\"><strong data-start=\"320\" data-end=\"336\">Description:</strong><br data-start=\"336\" data-end=\"339\" />L-Carnitine is a water-soluble quaternary ammonium compound naturally derived from lysine and methionine. This liquid formulation provides a highly concentration of L-Carnitine at <strong data-start=\"523\" data-end=\"536\">500 mg/mL</strong>, offering ease of use and consistent measurement for research applications. L-Carnitine plays a crucial role in mitochondrial energy metabolism by transporting long-chain fatty acids into the mitochondria for beta-oxidation. It is frequently studied in research focused on energy production, metabolic efficiency, fat oxidation, and athletic recovery.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"890\" data-end=\"893\" />\n<p data-start=\"895\" data-end=\"989\"><strong data-start=\"895\" data-end=\"921\">Research Applications:</strong><br data-start=\"921\" data-end=\"924\" />L-Carnitine (liquid) is commonly researched for its ability to:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"990\" data-end=\"1294\">\n<li data-start=\"990\" data-end=\"1059\">\n<p data-start=\"992\" data-end=\"1059\"><strong data-start=\"992\" data-end=\"1038\">Support Mitochondrial Fatty Acid Transport</strong> and ATP generation</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1060\" data-end=\"1135\">\n<p data-start=\"1062\" data-end=\"1135\"><strong data-start=\"1062\" data-end=\"1107\">Improve Physical Performance and Recovery</strong> during and after exertion</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1136\" data-end=\"1208\">\n<p data-start=\"1138\" data-end=\"1208\"><strong data-start=\"1138\" data-end=\"1172\">Facilitate Fat Loss Mechanisms</strong> through enhanced lipid metabolism</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1209\" data-end=\"1294\">\n<p data-start=\"1211\" data-end=\"1294\"><strong data-start=\"1211\" data-end=\"1258\">Enhance Cognitive and Cardiovascular Health</strong> under oxidative or metabolic stress</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1296\" data-end=\"1299\" />\n<p data-start=\"1301\" data-end=\"1328\"><strong data-start=\"1301\" data-end=\"1326\">Storage and Handling:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1329\" data-end=\"1479\">\n<li data-start=\"1329\" data-end=\"1383\">\n<p data-start=\"1331\" data-end=\"1383\">Store at <strong data-start=\"1340\" data-end=\"1360\">room temperature</strong> or between <strong data-start=\"1372\" data-end=\"1381\">2–8°C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1384\" data-end=\"1401\">\n<p data-start=\"1386\" data-end=\"1401\">Do not freeze</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1402\" data-end=\"1427\">\n<p data-start=\"1404\" data-end=\"1427\">Shake well before use</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1428\" data-end=\"1479\">\n<p data-start=\"1430\" data-end=\"1479\">Use sterile technique for withdrawal and handling</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1481\" data-end=\"1484\" />\n<p data-start=\"1486\" data-end=\"1515\"><strong data-start=\"1486\" data-end=\"1513\">Product Specifications:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1516\" data-end=\"1714\">\n<li data-start=\"1516\" data-end=\"1545\">\n<p data-start=\"1518\" data-end=\"1545\"><strong data-start=\"1518\" data-end=\"1527\">Form:</strong> Liquid Solution</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1546\" data-end=\"1578\">\n<p data-start=\"1548\" data-end=\"1578\"><strong data-start=\"1548\" data-end=\"1566\">Concentration:</strong> 500 mg/mL</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1579\" data-end=\"1615\">\n<p data-start=\"1581\" data-end=\"1615\"><strong data-start=\"1581\" data-end=\"1592\">Purity:</strong> ≥99% (HPLC Verified)</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1616\" data-end=\"1674\">\n<p data-start=\"1618\" data-end=\"1674\"><strong data-start=\"1618\" data-end=\"1633\">Appearance:</strong> Clear, colorless to pale yellow liquid</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1675\" data-end=\"1714\">\n<p data-start=\"1677\" data-end=\"1714\"><strong data-start=\"1677\" data-end=\"1692\">Solubility:</strong> Fully water-soluble</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr data-start=\"1716\" data-end=\"1719\" />\n<p data-start=\"1721\" data-end=\"1912\"><strong data-start=\"1721\" data-end=\"1740\">Important Note:</strong><br data-start=\"1740\" data-end=\"1743\" />This product is <strong data-start=\"1759\" data-end=\"1784\">FOR RESEARCH USE ONLY</strong>. Not for human or veterinary consumption. Unauthorized or off-label use is strictly prohibited and may violate applicable laws.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"1914\" data-end=\"1917\" />\n<p data-start=\"1919\" data-end=\"1936\"><strong data-start=\"1919\" data-end=\"1934\">References:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1937\" data-end=\"2273\">\n<li data-start=\"1937\" data-end=\"2041\">\n<p data-start=\"1939\" data-end=\"2041\">Brass, E. P. (2000). <em data-start=\"1960\" data-end=\"2000\">“Supplemental Carnitine and Exercise.”</em> American Journal of Clinical Nutrition</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2042\" data-end=\"2154\">\n<p data-start=\"2044\" data-end=\"2154\">Malaguarnera, M. (2012). <em data-start=\"2069\" data-end=\"2116\">“Carnitine Derivatives: Clinical Usefulness.”</em> Current Opinion in Gastroenterology</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"2155\" data-end=\"2273\">\n<p data-start=\"2157\" data-end=\"2273\">Stephens, F. B., et al. (2007). <em data-start=\"2189\" data-end=\"2251\">“Skeletal Muscle Carnitine Loading Increases Fat Oxidation.”</em> Journal of Physiology</p>\n</li>\n</ul>',100.00,60.00,NULL,500.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/lcar-scaled.jpeg','https://myoasislabs.com/product/carnitine-5000/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 19:50:02',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,44),(73,'BPC-157/TB-500 Blend 10/10mg','<p>All Oasis Labs products are third-party tested by clinical labs to ensure maximum purity.</p>',183.00,89.00,NULL,10.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/BPC-157TB-500-10-10mg-scaledB-scaled.png','https://myoasislabs.com/product/bpc-157-tb-500-blend-10-10mg/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 19:16:27',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,403),(74,'Selank 10mg','<p class=\"\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"68\"><strong data-start=\"20\" data-end=\"66\">Selank (Synthetic Heptapeptide Anxiolytic)</strong></p>\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"70\" data-end=\"73\" />\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"75\" data-end=\"102\"><strong data-start=\"75\" data-end=\"100\">Chemical Information:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"103\" data-end=\"323\">\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"103\" data-end=\"141\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"105\" data-end=\"141\"><strong data-start=\"105\" data-end=\"127\">Molecular Formula:</strong> C₃₃H₅₇N₁₁O₉</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"142\" data-end=\"180\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"144\" data-end=\"180\"><strong data-start=\"144\" data-end=\"165\">Molecular Weight:</strong> 751.88 g/mol</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"181\" data-end=\"226\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"183\" data-end=\"226\"><strong data-start=\"183\" data-end=\"196\">Sequence:</strong> Thr-Lys-Pro-Arg-Pro-Gly-Pro</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"227\" data-end=\"323\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"229\" data-end=\"323\"><strong data-start=\"229\" data-end=\"253\">Molecular Structure:</strong> Refer to Certificate of Analysis for detailed structural information.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"325\" data-end=\"328\" />\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"330\" data-end=\"872\"><strong data-start=\"330\" data-end=\"346\">Description:</strong><br data-start=\"346\" data-end=\"349\" />Selank is a synthetic heptapeptide developed as an analog of the naturally occurring tuftsin tetrapeptide. It has been widely researched for its potential anxiolytic, nootropic, and immunomodulatory properties. Selank is thought to influence neurotransmitter systems and has been investigated for its effects on cognitive function, stress modulation, and mood regulation. Supplied in lyophilized powder form, Selank is intended for use in controlled laboratory studies related to neurochemistry and behavioral neuroscience.</p>\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"874\" data-end=\"877\" />\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"879\" data-end=\"958\"><strong data-start=\"879\" data-end=\"905\">Research Applications:</strong><br data-start=\"905\" data-end=\"908\" />Selank is actively studied for its potential to:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"959\" data-end=\"1462\">\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"959\" data-end=\"1102\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"961\" data-end=\"1102\"><strong data-start=\"961\" data-end=\"993\">Modulate Anxiety and Stress:</strong> Investigate its effects on GABAergic activity and its potential anxiolytic effects in experimental models.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1103\" data-end=\"1205\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1105\" data-end=\"1205\"><strong data-start=\"1105\" data-end=\"1136\">Enhance Cognitive Function:</strong> Explore its influence on memory, attention, and learning capacity.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1206\" data-end=\"1343\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1208\" data-end=\"1343\"><strong data-start=\"1208\" data-end=\"1236\">Support Mood Regulation:</strong> Study its potential role in stabilizing mood and emotional response through neurotransmitter modulation.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1344\" data-end=\"1462\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1346\" data-end=\"1462\"><strong data-start=\"1346\" data-end=\"1383\">Examine Immunomodulatory Effects:</strong> Research its potential influence on immune response and inflammation pathways.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1464\" data-end=\"1467\" />\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1469\" data-end=\"1496\"><strong data-start=\"1469\" data-end=\"1494\">Storage and Handling:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1497\" data-end=\"1678\">\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1497\" data-end=\"1539\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1499\" data-end=\"1539\">Store lyophilized powder at <strong data-start=\"1527\" data-end=\"1536\">-20°C</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1540\" data-end=\"1600\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1542\" data-end=\"1600\">Once reconstituted, store at <strong data-start=\"1571\" data-end=\"1580\">2-8°C</strong> and use promptly.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1601\" data-end=\"1678\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1603\" data-end=\"1678\">Use aseptic techniques during handling to maintain sterility and integrity.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1680\" data-end=\"1683\" />\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1685\" data-end=\"1714\"><strong data-start=\"1685\" data-end=\"1712\">Product Specifications:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"1715\" data-end=\"1846\">\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1715\" data-end=\"1751\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1717\" data-end=\"1751\"><strong data-start=\"1717\" data-end=\"1728\">Purity:</strong> ≥99% (HPLC Verified)</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1752\" data-end=\"1796\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1754\" data-end=\"1796\"><strong data-start=\"1754\" data-end=\"1769\">Appearance:</strong> Lyophilized white powder</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1797\" data-end=\"1846\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1799\" data-end=\"1846\"><strong data-start=\"1799\" data-end=\"1814\">Solubility:</strong> Soluble in bacteriostatic water</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1848\" data-end=\"1851\" />\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1853\" data-end=\"2436\"><strong data-start=\"1853\" data-end=\"1872\">Important Note:</strong><br data-start=\"1872\" data-end=\"1875\" />Selank is strictly <strong data-start=\"1894\" data-end=\"1919\">FOR RESEARCH USE ONLY</strong> and is intended exclusively for in vitro research and laboratory experimentation by qualified professionals. It is <strong data-start=\"2035\" data-end=\"2042\">not</strong> a drug, food, cosmetic, or dietary supplement and has not been evaluated by the FDA. This peptide is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Introduction into humans or animals is strictly prohibited by law. Any misuse, misbranding, or mislabeling is a violation of federal regulations and may result in legal consequences under applicable federal, state, or local laws.</p>\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2438\" data-end=\"2441\" />\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2443\" data-end=\"2504\"><strong data-start=\"2443\" data-end=\"2458\">References:</strong><br data-start=\"2458\" data-end=\"2461\" />Referenced scientific publications include:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"2506\" data-end=\"2802\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2506\" data-end=\"2657\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2508\" data-end=\"2657\">Seredenin, S. B., et al. (2008). <em data-start=\"2541\" data-end=\"2608\">“Pharmacological Activity of Selank, a Novel Anxiolytic Peptide.”</em> Bulletin of Experimental Biology and Medicine.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2658\" data-end=\"2802\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2660\" data-end=\"2802\">Andreeva, L. A., et al. (2015). <em data-start=\"2692\" data-end=\"2762\">“Selank as a Peptide Drug with Anxiolytic and Nootropic Properties.”</em> Neuroscience and Behavioral Physiology.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>',84.00,42.00,NULL,10.00,'in_stock','active',2,NULL,0,0,0,'https://myoasislabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Selank-scaled.jpg','https://myoasislabs.com/product/selank-10mg/','2025-12-04 13:37:06','2025-12-04 13:37:06',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,68),(75,'Semax 10mg','<p class=\"\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"59\"><strong data-start=\"20\" data-end=\"57\">Semax (ACTH-Derived Neuropeptide)</strong></p>\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"61\" data-end=\"64\" />\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"66\" data-end=\"93\"><strong data-start=\"66\" data-end=\"91\">Chemical Information:</strong></p>\n<ul data-start=\"94\" data-end=\"315\">\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"94\" data-end=\"133\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"96\" data-end=\"133\"><strong data-start=\"96\" data-end=\"118\">Molecular Formula:</strong> C₃₇H₅₁N₉O₁₀S</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"134\" data-end=\"172\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"136\" data-end=\"172\"><strong data-start=\"136\" data-end=\"157\">Molecular Weight:</strong> 813.93 g/mol</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"173\" data-end=\"218\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"175\" data-end=\"218\"><strong data-start=\"175\" data-end=\"188\">Sequence:</strong> Met-Glu-His-Phe-Pro-Gly-Pro</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"219\" data-end=\"315\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"221\" data-end=\"315\"><strong data-start=\"221\" data-end=\"245\">Molecular Structure:</strong> Refer to Certificate of Analysis for detailed structural information.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"317\" data-end=\"320\" />\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"322\" data-end=\"797\"><strong data-start=\"322\" data-end=\"338\">Description:</strong><b