</strong> receptors (Reta) and <strong>Amylin</strong> receptors (Cagri).  The effects from these compounds are being studied for regulating <strong>Ghrelin</strong> (hunger hormone) production, breaking down white adipose tissue (<strong>fat</strong>) into free fatty acids to be converted into <strong>ATP</strong>, increasing brown adipose tissue activity (<strong>energy</strong> <strong>metabolism</strong> and thermogenesis), and <strong>reducing</strong> the presence of various <strong>diseases</strong> related to the liver, inflammation, and obesity.</p>',135.00,NULL,NULL,12.50,'in_stock','active',3,NULL,0,0,0,'https://alphaomegapeptide.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/RETACAG-Peptide-Vial.png','https://alphaomegapeptide.com/products/retacag/','2025-12-04 14:02:16','2025-12-04 14:02:16',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,98),(120,'Humanin','<p data-start=\"129\" data-end=\"294\"><strong>Humanin</strong> is a mitochondrial-derived peptide studied for its role in cellular protection, stress response, and healthy cellular aging.  It is being explored for it&#8217;s role in neuroprotective and metabolic dysfunction as well as anti-aging research.  Humanin has shown promise in a<span style=\"font-size: 16px\">ctivating signaling pathways tied to cellular defense and repair, </span><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">cell survival, and anti-apoptotic activity.</span></p>',99.00,NULL,NULL,NULL,'in_stock','active',3,NULL,0,0,0,'https://alphaomegapeptide.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Humanin-10MG.png','https://alphaomegapeptide.com/products/humanin/','2025-12-04 14:02:16','2025-12-04 14:02:16',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,99),(121,'Thymosin Alpha-1 (Tα-1)','<p class=\"ai-optimize-28 ai-optimize-introduction\"><strong>Thymosin Alpha-1</strong> is a research-grade peptide studied for its role in immune regulation, T-cell activity, and overall immune pathway support.  It is widely for its role in supporting immune balance that influences both innate and adaptive immune activity.</p>',86.00,NULL,NULL,NULL,'in_stock','active',3,NULL,0,0,0,'https://alphaomegapeptide.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Thymosin-Alpha-1.png','https://alphaomegapeptide.com/products/thymosin-alpha-1/','2025-12-04 14:02:16','2025-12-04 14:02:16',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,100),(122,'FOXO4-DRI 10MG','<div class=\"product-description\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0 0 1.5em !important\"><strong>FOXO4-DRI</strong> is a cell-penetrating research peptide studied for its ability to target and remove senescent cells—aged cells that no longer divide. In scientific studies, it has been shown to selectively trigger apoptosis (programmed cell death) in these cells, helping researchers explore ways to slow or reverse signs of aging in animal models.</p>\n<ul style=\"margin: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em !important\">\n<li>Targets senescent cells to study their link to aging and tissue decline</li>\n<li>Supports research on cell turnover, tissue health, and regeneration</li>\n<li>Used in animal studies to explore potential anti-aging pathways</li>\n</ul>\n</div>',180.00,NULL,NULL,10.00,'in_stock','active',3,NULL,0,0,0,'https://alphaomegapeptide.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/FOX04-DRI.png','https://alphaomegapeptide.com/products/fox04-dri/','2025-12-04 14:02:16','2025-12-04 20:52:07',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,386),(123,'GLP-3RT 12MG','<div class=\"product-description\">\n<p>GLP-3RT 12MG IS ON BACKORDER UNTIL FRIDAY DECEMBER 5TH.</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0 0 1.5em !important\"><strong>GLP-3RT 12MG</strong> is a lab-made tri-agonist peptide that works on <strong>GLP-1</strong>, <strong>GIP</strong>, and <strong>glucagon receptors</strong>. Researchers use it to study obesity, metabolism, and heart health. This peptide gives scientists a simple and reliable way to explore how three hormone receptors work together in lab studies.</p>\n<ul style=\"margin: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em !important;padding: 0 !important\">\n<li>Works on GLP-1, GIP, and glucagon receptors for clear metabolic research.</li>\n<li>Supports studies on energy use, blood sugar balance, and