NULL,'in_stock','active',4,NULL,0,0,0,'https://purerawz.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Melanotan-1-Peptide-PRZ-2-1.webp','https://purerawz.co/product/melanotan/','2025-12-04 14:51:10','2025-12-04 14:51:10',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,223),(287,'AICAR','<ul>\n<li>1st and 3rd Party Verified for 99% Purity</li>\n<li>Free Shipping on Orders Over $100+</li>\n</ul>',71.53,NULL,NULL,NULL,'in_stock','active',4,NULL,0,0,0,'https://purerawz.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/AICAR-50mg-1-1.webp','https://purerawz.co/product/aicar/','2025-12-04 14:51:10','2025-12-04 14:51:10',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,224),(288,'S-Acetyl L-Glutathione','<ul>\n<li>1st and 3rd Party Verified for 99% Purity</li>\n<li>Free Shipping on Orders Over $100+</li>\n</ul>',22.22,NULL,NULL,NULL,'in_stock','active',4,NULL,0,0,0,'https://purerawz.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/S-Acetyl-L-Glutathione-60tabs_Purz-1.webp','https://purerawz.co/product/s-acetyl-l-glutathione/','2025-12-04 14:51:10','2025-12-04 14:51:10',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,225),(289,'Mirodenafil','<ul>\n<li>1st and 3rd Party Verified for 99% Purity</li>\n<li>Free Shipping on Orders Over $100+</li>\n</ul>',58.30,NULL,NULL,NULL,'in_stock','active',4,NULL,0,0,0,'https://purerawz.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Mirodenafil-Liquid-30ml-33mg-3-1.webp','https://purerawz.co/product/mirodenafil/','2025-12-04 14:51:10','2025-12-04 14:51:10',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,226),(290,'4-Andro','<h2>4-Andro &#8211; Product Information</h2>\n<p>4-Andro&#8217;s main ingredient, 4-Dehydroepiandrosterone (4-DHEA), is a positional isomer of the DHEA compound. The chemical structural modification of DHEA reduces its thermogenic properties (calorie burning) while increasing its androgenic and anabolic properties and endothelial nitric oxide synthase activity by increasing its potential binding affinity to muscular receptors.</p>\n<p>A recent study on the physiological and hormonal influence of androstenedione found that during 12 weeks of androstenedione or androstenediol use, a significant increase in the aromatization by-products estrone and estradiol was observed in research subjects. In the dione group, total testosterone levels significantly increased by 16% after 1 month of use, but by the end of 12 weeks, they returned to pre-treatment levels.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"301\"><strong>4-Andro</strong></td>\n<td width=\"301\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"301\"><strong>CAS Number</strong></td>\n<td width=\"301\"><strong>1156-92-9</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"301\"><strong>Molar Mass</strong></td>\n<td width=\"301\"><strong>290,44 g/mol</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"301\"><strong>Chemical Formula</strong></td>\n<td width=\"301\"><strong>C19H30O2</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"301\"><strong>IUPAC Name </strong></td>\n<td width=\"301\"><strong>(3S,8R,9S,10R,13S,14S,17S)-10,13-dimethyl-2,3,6,7,8,9,11,12,14,15,16,17-dodecahydro-1H-cyclopenta[a]phenanthrene-3,17-diol</strong></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<h2>What is 4-Andro?</h2>\n<p>4-Andro, also known as 4 Androstenediol, is a chemical known as prohormone. The body has the ability to convert prohormones into anabolic hormones, which, in turn, help stimulate muscle growth and generate protein synthesis. Some of these anabolic hormones include testosterone. [<a href=\"https://www.verywellfit.com/are-prohormones-safe-to-use-4773941\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>4-Andro is produced naturally in the body by the adrenal glands, as well as the testes and the ovaries. It acts as a precursor in testosterone and estrogen hormone production. That is to say that the body could potentially use endogenous 4 Andro to produce testosterone and estrogen. [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/7911183\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>DHEA, the main ingredient of 4-Andro, is often referred to as the &#8220;mother of all hormones.&#8221; That is because it is the building block from which male and female hormones are produced. The naturally occurring DHEA isomer is produced inside the body.</p>\n<p>DHEA&#8217;s production declines as you age, especially in your mid-thirties to forties. This leads to a deficiency that can make you feel physically and mentally exhausted. Research has shown that DHEA replacement may have the ability to improve the function of the immune system and increases energy. [<a href=\"https://www.foreverhealth.com/blogs/forever-health/69755973-dhea\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<h2>How Does 4-Andro Work?</h2>\n<p>Current research studies are examining the body&#8217;s potential to convert exogenous 4- Andro into other chemicals such as hormones. Some of these potential hormones include testosterone and estrogen.</p>\n<p>Testosterone in males regulates sex drive, bone mass, fat distribution, and muscle mass and strength. [<a href=\"https://www.webmd.com/vitamins/ai/ingredientmono-1553/4-androsterone\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>][<a href=\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/understanding-how-testosterone-affects-men#:~:text=Testosterone is a sex hormone,estradiol, a form of estrogen.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>Additionally, it has been found that the conversion rate of 4-Andro to testosterone has massive potential, with research showing a ratio as high as 15.76%. This is almost triple that of 4-androstenedione, another androstenediol. The difference is due to the utilization of different enzymatic pathways by 4 Andro. [<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/4-Androstenediol\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<h2>Androstenediol Vs Androstenedione</h2>\n<p>Androstenediol (4-Andro) and Androstenedione are both precursors of testosterone.</p>\n<p>Both are produced by the adrenal glands, as well as the testes and ovaries. In men, the body uses both these hormones to produce testosterone. In women, these hormones act as intermediaries to estrogen, a hormone that gives women feminine characteristics.</p>\n<p>Despite sharing these many similarities, a few differences exist between Androstenediol and Androstenedione. In contrast to Androstenediol or 4 Andro, Androstenedione has a very low affinity for the estrogen receptors, including less than 0.01% affinity for ERα and ERβ. [<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1210/endo.138.3.4979\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<h2>4-Andro Research</h2>\n<p>Multiple human studies have shown that one of the main ingredients of 4-Andro may possess the potential to increase serum IGF-1 levels in the body. These studies have also found DHEA to have possible positive impacts on knee muscle strength and lumbar back strength in males.</p>\n<h3>4-Andro and IGF-1</h3>\n<p>Dehydroepiandrosterone (DHEA) is the main active ingredient of 4-Andro. A study found that administration of a 50mg daily dose of DHEA for 3 months to age-advanced men and women resulted in an elevation (10%) of serum levels of insulin-like growth factor-1 (IGF-1). [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9876338/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>The findings from this study led researchers to assess the effect of a larger dose (100 mg) of DHEA for a longer duration (6 months) on circulating sex steroids, body composition, and muscle strength. An increase in serum IGF-1 levels was observed in both genders. [<a href=\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1046/j.1365-2265.1998.00507.x\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>Insulin-like growth factor 1 (IGF-1) is a hormone that manages the effects of growth hormone (GH) in your body. It also mediates the protein anabolic and linear growth-promoting effect of pituitary GH. Together, IGF-1 and GH promote the natural growth of bones and tissues. [<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1187088/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<h3>4-Andro and Testosterone</h3>\n<p>Testosterone is an important androgenic growth hormone. It regulates tissue repair, secondary sex characteristics, and various growth functions. In men, it&#8217;s thought to regulate sex drive, bone mass, fat distribution, muscle mass and strength, and the production of sperm. [<a href=\"https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/understanding-how-testosterone-affects-men#:~:text=Testosterone is a sex hormone,estradiol, a form of estrogen.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>In a study conducted in 2000, the effects of 200 mg/day oral administration of Androstenedione or 4-Andro were observed. It was found that both free and total serum testosterone concentrations were significantly elevated by the 4-week measurement period (p &lt; .05). [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12671199/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>Similarly, a 2013 study found that taking 50 mg of DHEA per day raised the free testosterone levels of middle-aged adults undergoing high-intensity interval training (HIIT). Therefore, DHEA supplementation may have significant potential benefits related to HIIT adaptation. [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23417481/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<h3>4-Andro and The Potential Implications for Muscle Strength</h3>\n<p>In the abovementioned study, the effects of 100mg of DHEA on muscle strength were also observed. It was found that in men, but not in women, knee muscle strength 15.063.3% (P ¼0.02), as well as lumbar back strength 13.965.4% (p ¼0.01), increased.</p>\n<p>The increase in knee strength in men may be of particular value. That is because knee weakness is strongly correlated to falls and morbidity in the elderly. The mechanism by which the increase occurred in men in response to DHEA is currently unknown.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, these differences in response to DHEA administration between males and females may reflect a gender-specific response to DHEA and/or the presence of confounding factor(s) in women, such as estrogen replacement therapy.</p>\n<h3>4-Andro and Potential Effects on Depression</h3>\n<p>A recent study set out to investigate whether DHEA is more effective than a placebo in the treatment of depressive symptoms. All the subjects had depression not resulting from other psychiatric conditions or medical comorbidities.</p>\n<p>The meta-analysis applied in this review pointed to a significant effect in favor of treatment with DHEA compared to placebo. It concluded that DHEA might be a more effective alternative to the compounds used in the treatment of depression. [<a href=\"http://www.eurekaselect.com/article/92479\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>In another study, six middle-aged and elderly patients with major depression were openly administered DHEA. Preliminary data from the study suggest DHEA may have antidepressant and pro-memory effects. The data should encourage double-blind trials in depressed patients. [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9024954/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<h3>4-Andro and Potential on Weight</h3>\n<p>DHEA administration has been shown to reduce abdominal visceral fat accumulation and protect against insulin resistance in lab animals. A double-blind, placebo-controlled study was conducted to determine whether DHEA therapy decreases abdominal fat in elderly humans.</p>\n<p>Compared with the placebo, the 6 months of DHEA replacement resulted in decreased body weight (2.4kg vs. 0.6kg), with no difference in response between men and women. Significant decreases in abdominal visceral fat occurred during the 6 months of DHEA replacement. [<a href=\"https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/fullarticle/199765\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>It is not known if DHEA helps younger patients to lose weight.</p>\n<h3>4-Andro and The Potential Relevance to Mood</h3>\n<p>A study was carried out to investigate the effects of DHEA administration in healthy young men. DHEA administration led to a reduction in evening cortisol concentrations and improved mood and memory. Recollection accuracy in the episodic memory test was also significantly improved. [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16231168/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>Another study demonstrated that DHEA reduced activity in the amygdala and hippocampus, enhanced connectivity between the amygdala and hippocampus, and enhanced activity in the rACC. These results demonstrate that DHEA may potentially reduce activity in regions associated with the generation of negative emotions. [<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3717538/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>Considering that activity in these regions is altered in mood and anxiety disorders, our results provide initial neuroimaging evidence that DHEA may potentially be useful as a pharmacological intervention for these conditions.</p>\n<h3>4-Andro and Potential Effect on Skin</h3>\n<p>Topical DHEA may potentially improve skin brightness and counteracts the papery appearance of skin and epidermal atrophy, a characteristic feature of hormone-related skin aging. Topical DHEA could also potentially act on skin processes related to wrinkles, but this result remains to be confirmed. [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18242894/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>Data from another study suggest the possibility that topical DHEA could be used as an efficient and physiological anti-aging skin agent. This study was a placebo-controlled, randomized, prospective study performed with 75 postmenopausal women aged 60-65 years. [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20698844/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>A clinical trial was also conducted to determine the response of skin parameters related to skin aging to the local action of DHEA in postmenopausal women. Unfortunately, the trial results are yet to be published, even though the study has been complete since 2008. [<a href=\"https://clinicaltrials.gov/ct2/show/results/NCT00248989\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<h3>4-Andro and The Potential to Aid Sexual Dysfunction</h3>\n<p>An analysis was conducted to review the contemporary knowledge regarding DHEA and erectile dysfunction (ED). It was observed that low levels of DHEA were associated with a higher risk for ED in men, and low sexual responsiveness in women. [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16140085\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>][<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17208951\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<p>However, there were no significant differences in sexual performance outcomes between placebo or DHEA groups in 79 men with sexual dysfunction and androgen deficiency in a more recent study. In a separate study, DHEA improved feelings of well-being but not libido in older males. [<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19883295\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>][<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/8788227\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<h2>4 -Andro FAQs</h2>\n<h3>Does DHEA have the potential to build lean muscle mass?</h3>\n<p>A new study shows that DHEA and Androstenedione don&#8217;t affect muscle mass, body fat concentration, or aerobic capacity. Furthermore, neither Androstenedione nor DHEA affects lean tissue growth. [<a href=\"https://www.webmd.com/fitness-exercise/news/20000106/andro-dhea#:~:text=Theoretically, androstenedione and DHEA should,muscular strength, or aerobic capacity.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>R</strong></a>]</p>\n<h3>Is 4-Androsterone legal?</h3>\n<p>4-Andro is legal to buy and sell as a research chemical only.</p>\n<h3>Where to Buy 4-Andro Online</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://purerawz.co/\">PureRawz</a> is the best place to buy 4 Andro online.</p>\n<p>In order to be the best research chemicals supplier, we provide reference materials with every product we sell. Each of our products comes with an independent, third-party-issued <a href=\"https://purerawz.co/certificate-of-analysis/\">Certificate of Analysis</a> for identification, purity, and concentration.</p>\n<p>We offer free international shipping on all orders above $100. You can pay for your purchase through various methods, including PayPal and Bitcoin. Click on the &#8216;Reviews&#8217; tab to check out what existing customers have to say about our products and great customer service.</p>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div class=\"row item-row\">\n<div class=\"col-xs-24\">\n<div class=\"row item-row\">\n<div class=\"col-xs-24\">\n<div><strong>Disclaimer</strong></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>This information is for educational purposes only and does not constitute medical advice. THE PRODUCTS DESCRIBED HEREIN ARE FOR LABORATORY AND RESEARCH USE ONLY. All clinical research must be conducted with oversight from the appropriate Institutional Review Board (IRB). All preclinical research must be conducted with oversight from the appropriate Institutional Animal Care and Use Committee (IACUC) following the guidelines of the Animal Welfare Act (AWA).</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Our content is intended to be used and must be used for informational purposes only. It is very important to do your own analysis and research from Trusted Sources before making any purchase bas