wth hormone modulation, tissue repair, and metabolic studies.</p>',25.00,NULL,NULL,5.00,'in_stock','active',6,NULL,0,0,0,'https://purehealthpeptides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Ipamorelin-1.jpg','https://purehealthpeptides.com/product/ipamorelin/','2025-12-04 15:07:17','2025-12-04 15:07:17',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,56),(500,'LL-37','<p><strong>LL-37</strong> is a naturally occurring antimicrobial peptide derived from the human cathelicidin protein. It is well-known for its ability to modulate immune responses, promote wound healing, and combat bacterial, viral, and fungal pathogens. LL-37 is provided in lyophilized powder form for research purposes exploring its role in immunity, inflammation, and tissue regeneration.</p>',69.00,NULL,NULL,5.00,'in_stock','active',6,NULL,0,0,0,'https://purehealthpeptides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LL-37-1.jpg','https://purehealthpeptides.com/product/ll-37/','2025-12-04 15:07:17','2025-12-04 15:07:17',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,31),(501,'BPC-157/TB-500','<p><strong>BPC-157/TB-500</strong> is a synthetic peptide blend combining two potent compounds: <strong>BPC-157</strong>, derived from Body Protection Compound, and <strong>TB-500</strong>, a synthetic version of Thymosin Beta-4. These peptides are extensively studied for their synergistic properties in supporting tissue repair, wound healing, and overall recovery in laboratory research applications. Supplied in lyophilized powder form for maximum stability.</p>',52.00,NULL,NULL,5.00,'out_of_stock','active',6,NULL,0,0,0,'https://purehealthpeptides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/BPC-157_TB-500.jpg','https://purehealthpeptides.com/product/bpc-157-tb-500/','2025-12-04 15:07:17','2025-12-04 19:16:27',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,403),(502,'BPC-157','<p><strong>BPC-157</strong> is a synthetic peptide fragment derived from a naturally occurring protein found in gastric juice. It has been studied extensively in laboratory settings for its potential to support tissue regeneration and cell protection. This pep