:28:45','2025-12-04 17:28:45',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,415),(685,'FOXO4-DRI','<p data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"437\"><strong>FOXO4-DRI</strong> is a specialized research peptide known for its ability to enter cells and interact with pathways linked to cellular aging. Researchers use it to study how clearing senescent cells, those that have stopped dividing, may influence tissue repair and longevity. Through controlled studies, FOXO4-DRI helps scientists examine how selective removal of these cells affects aging markers and overall cellular balance in animal models.</p>\n<ul>\n<li data-start=\"441\" data-end=\"518\">Investigates senescent cell clearance and its connection to aging processes</li>\n<li data-start=\"441\" data-end=\"518\">Aids in studies of cellular renewal, tissue recovery, and regenerative activity</li>\n<li data-start=\"605\" data-end=\"690\">Utilized in animal research to assess potential longevity and anti-aging mechanisms</li>\n</ul>',180.00,NULL,NULL,NULL,'in_stock','active',9,NULL,0,0,0,'https://simplepeptide.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/FOX04-DRI-Wide.png','https://simplepeptide.com/product/fox-04-dri/','2025-12-04 17:28:45','2025-12-04 20:52:07',0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,386),(686,'GLP-3RT 6MG','<p class=\"ai-optimize-43\"><strong>GLP-3RT is a GGG tri-agonist that targets GLP-1 and GIP receptors, akin to standard GLP-1 agonists, but also uniquely activates the glucagon receptor.</strong></p>\n<p class=\"ai-optimize-44\"><strong>Clinical Data:</strong></p>\n<p class=\"ai-optimize-45\"><a href=\"https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa2301972\">GLP-3RT: Triple–Hormone-Receptor Agonist for Obesity — A Phase 2 Trial</a></p>\n<p class=\"ai-optimize-46\"><a href=\"https://trials.lilly.com/en-US/trial/405675\">GLP-3RT: A Study (LY3437943) in Participants With Obesity and Cardiovascular Disease (TRIUMPH-3)</a></p>\n<p class=\"heading-title ai-optimize-47\"><a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37366315/\">GLP-3RT: Triple-Hormone-Receptor Agonist Study for 